@subsubsection Strings in Component Values

@node Special Characters in Pathname Components, Case in Pathname Components, Strings in Component Values, Interpreting Pathname Component Values
@subsubsection Special Characters in Pathname Components

@i{Strings} in @i{pathname} component values 
never contain special @i{characters} that represent
separation between @i{pathname} fields, 
such as @i{slash} in @r{Unix} @i{filenames}.
Whether separator @i{characters} are permitted as 
part of a @i{string} in a @i{pathname} component
is @i{implementation-defined}; 
however, if the @i{implementation} does permit it, 
it must arrange to properly ``quote'' the character for the 
@i{file system} when constructing a @i{namestring}.
For example,

@example
 ;; In a TOPS-20 implementation, which uses @t{^}V to quote 
 (NAMESTRING (MAKE-PATHNAME :HOST "OZ" :NAME "<TEST>"))
@result{}  #P"OZ:PS:@t{^}V<TEST@t{^}V>"
@i{NOT}@result{} #P"OZ:PS:<TEST>"
@end example

