@subsubsection Case in Pathname Components

@i{Namestrings} always use local file system @i{case} conventions, 
but @r{Common Lisp} @i{functions} that manipulate @i{pathname} components
allow the caller to select either of two conventions for representing
@i{case} in component values by supplying a value for the
@t{:case} keyword argument.
Figure 19--2 lists the functions 
relating to @i{pathnames} that permit a @t{:case} argument:

