@subsection *default-pathname-defaults*                                      [Variable]

@subsubheading  Value Type::

a @i{pathname} @i{object}.

@subsubheading  Initial Value::

An @i{implementation-dependent} @i{pathname}, 
typically in the working directory that was current when @r{Common Lisp} was started up.

@subsubheading  Description::

a @i{pathname}, used as the default whenever a @i{function}
needs a default @i{pathname} and one is not supplied.

@subsubheading  Examples::                                                   
@example
 ;; This example illustrates a possible usage for a hypothetical Lisp running on a
 ;; DEC TOPS-20 file system.  Since pathname conventions vary between Lisp 
 ;; implementations and host file system types, it is not possible to provide a
 ;; general-purpose, conforming example.
 *default-pathname-defaults* @result{}  #P"PS:<FRED>"
 (merge-pathnames (make-pathname :name "CALENDAR"))
@result{}  #P"PS:<FRED>CALENDAR"
 (let ((*default-pathname-defaults* (pathname "<MARY>")))
   (merge-pathnames (make-pathname :name "CALENDAR")))
@result{}  #P"<MARY>CALENDAR"
@end example

@subsubheading  Affected By::

The @i{implementation}.

